eNCA's Aviwe Mtila has more details. Courtesy #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - The High Court in Johannesburg has heard that then National Police Commissioner Riah Phiyega sent angry police officers to confront striking Lonmin mineworkers. The lawyer for the mineworkers, Dali Mpofu, has been arguing a civil claim against President Cyril Ramaphosa, Sibanye-Stillwater Mine and the government. Thirty-four mineworkers were gunned down by the police in August 2012 in what became known as the Marikana Massacre. Watch the video above for more details.